==English==

===Adverb===
'''quindicessima'''

====Etymology====
Borrowed from Italian '''quindicessima''', the feminine ordinal form of '''[[quindici]]''', meaning "fifteen"
====Meaning====
#(''Music'') Two octaves higher. Marking indicates a passage to be transposed up two octaves. Abbreviation: [[15ma]].

